(Forensic Probing Playbook: Finding the Offending Service) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Think like an incident investigator. Your job is not to guess. Your job is to build evidence,) Tj
T*
(narrow suspects, and identify the service that caused failure first.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Investigation Principles) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Start with timeline, not assumptions.) Tj
T*
(- Separate symptom service from root-cause service.) Tj
T*
(- Verify each claim with at least one command output.) Tj
T*
(- Use repeatable probe order so different people reach same conclusion.) Tj
T*
(- Track both process state \(running\) and readiness state \(able to serve traffic\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Service Map \(Suspect Graph\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- User hits web on localhost:3001.) Tj
T*
(- web depends on api \(http://api:3000\).) Tj
T*
(- api depends on redis \(redis://redis:6379\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If web fails, culprit may still be api or redis.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Failure Signatures in This System) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- api /healthz = 200, api /readyz = 503: API process alive, dependency not ready \(often Redis\).) Tj
T*
(- web / = 503 dependency unavailable: web cannot get a good upstream response after retries.) Tj
T*
(- Redis restarted and shortly after API readiness drops: likely dependency outage, not API code) Tj
T*
(bug.) Tj
T*
(- Container unhealthy in docker compose ps: probe command is failing repeatedly.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step-by-Step Investigation Workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step 1: Establish Scene Status) Tj
T*
(    docker compose ps) Tj
T*
(What to check:) Tj
T*
(- Are all three containers up?) Tj
T*
(- Which container is starting / healthy / unhealthy?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step 2: Build a Shared Timeline) Tj
T*
(    docker compose logs -f web api redis) Tj
T*
(What to check:) Tj
T*
(- First error timestamp.) Tj
T*
(- Which service logged problems first.) Tj
T*
(- Did downstream services fail after upstream dependency events?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step 3: Probe Health vs Readiness) Tj
T*
(    curl -i http://localhost:3000/healthz) Tj
T*
(    curl -i http://localhost:3000/readyz) Tj
T*
(    curl -i http://localhost:3001) Tj
ET
endstream
