(Interpretation:) Tj
T*
(- healthz=200 + readyz=503 means API process is alive but not ready for traffic.) Tj
T*
(- web=503 with API readiness failures usually means upstream dependency chain issue.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step 4: Inspect Dependency Directly) Tj
T*
(    docker compose exec redis redis-cli) Tj
T*
(    PING) Tj
T*
(    INCR visits) Tj
T*
(    GET visits) Tj
T*
(What to check:) Tj
T*
(- Does Redis respond immediately?) Tj
T*
(- Are read/write commands successful?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step 5: Validate In-Container Network Path) Tj
T*
(    docker compose exec api wget -qO- http://localhost:3000/readyz) Tj
T*
(    docker compose exec api sh) Tj
T*
(What to check:) Tj
T*
(- Does API report readiness from inside its own container?) Tj
T*
(- If needed, run more checks from inside container network context.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step 6: Controlled Failure Injection \(Reproduce\)) Tj
T*
(    docker compose restart redis) Tj
T*
(Then repeat Steps 1-5 while collecting timestamps.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Goal:) Tj
T*
(- Confirm whether failures are transient and recoverable or persistent.) Tj
T*
(- Confirm offending service by seeing who fails first, not who reports last.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Root-Cause Decision Tree) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- If redis unhealthy/unreachable first -> likely Redis root cause.) Tj
T*
(- If Redis healthy but api /readyz fails -> likely API logic/config issue.) Tj
T*
(- If API ready but web still fails -> likely web retry/upstream handling issue.) Tj
T*
(- If all probes pass but user still reports issue -> inspect request path details and stale) Tj
T*
(client/browser assumptions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Evidence Log Template) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Use this template while investigating:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    # Incident Notes) Tj
T*
(    - Time observed:) Tj
T*
(    - Trigger action \(if any\):) Tj
T*
(    - `docker compose ps` summary:) Tj
T*
(    - First error log line \(service + timestamp\):) Tj
T*
(    - `api /healthz` result:) Tj
T*
(    - `api /readyz` result:) Tj
T*
(    - `web /` result:) Tj
