(Fix Strategy by Offender) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Offender: Redis) Tj
T*
(- Check restart loops, resource pressure, or config issues.) Tj
T*
(- Keep API readiness dependent on actual Redis PING success.) Tj
T*
(- Allow temporary degradation and recovery instead of hard crash.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Offender: API) Tj
T*
(- Confirm REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379 in Compose.) Tj
T*
(- Ensure /readyz checks real dependency path.) Tj
T*
(- Avoid reporting ready when dependency calls fail.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Offender: Web) Tj
T*
(- Increase retry attempts/backoff for transient upstream outages.) Tj
T*
(- Return explicit 503 with context when upstream unavailable.) Tj
T*
(- Avoid permanent failure state after dependency recovers.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Closure Checklist) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Root cause identified with command evidence.) Tj
T*
(- Fix applied to offending service.) Tj
T*
(- docker compose ps returns healthy steady state.) Tj
T*
(- Endpoint probes \(/healthz, /readyz, /\) pass as expected.) Tj
T*
(- Failure injection \(restart redis\) confirms graceful recovery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A forensic workflow is successful when another investigator can replay your notes and reach the) Tj
T*
(same conclusion.) Tj
